g was associated with SF-36 mental component score (\textit{P} = .08), social interaction measured with the Friendship Scale (\textit{P} = .045), and CES-D score (\textit{P}=.04).{\textless}/p{\textgreater}{\textless}p{\textgreater}\textbf{CONCLUSIONS} Mobile sensing of sociability and activity is well correlated with traditional measures and less prone to biases associated with questionnaires that rely on recall. Using mobile devices to collect data from and monitor older adult patients has the potential to improve detection of changes in their health.{\textless}/p{\textgreater}},
